Over the past couple of days, I&#39;ve been learning about the JavaScript Event Loop.

A lot of the sources I&#39;ve found state that the Event Loop only pushes macrotask onto the Call Stack if the Call Stack is empty. However, an example presented by Jake Archibald shows the opposite.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const button = document.getElementsByTagName(&#39;button&#39;)[0];

    button.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {
      Promise.resolve().then(() =&gt; console.log(&#39;Microtask 1&#39;));
      console.log(&#39;Listener 1&#39;);
    });

    button.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, () =&gt; {
      Promise.resolve().then(() =&gt; console.log(&#39;Microtask 2&#39;));
      console.log(&#39;Listener 2&#39;);
    });

    button.click();


&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
    &lt;html&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;button&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;footer&gt;
        &lt;script type=&#39;text/javascript&#39; src=&#39;./src/index.js&#39;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/footer&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;


&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

When a user clicks the button, it acts as expected:

1. `onClick` is added to Call Stack
2. `Promise then` is added to Microtask Queue
3. `onClick` is removed from Call Stack
4. `Promise then` is added to Call Stack
5. `Promise then` is removed from Call Stack
6. 1 to 5 repeats for second `onClick`

When it&#39;s programatically clicked, you get the following:

1. `script` is added to Call Stack
2. `onClick` is added to Call Stack
3. `Promise then` is added to Microtask Queue
4. `onClick` is removed from Call Stack
6. 2 to 4 repeats for second `onClick`
7. `script` is removed from Call Stack
8. Microtask Queue is run

[Video Demo][1] (Starts at 32:05)

**Question:** What&#39;s different about this example that allows the macrotasks to be added to the Call Stack even when it&#39;s not empty?


